, modify, or even change prevailing sentiments and norms of behavior. For each topic, they include six engaging and accessible stories that conclude with short life lessons. Whether you're a fan of The Big Bang Theory or Seinfeld, the Beatles or Beyoncé, Charlie Brown or Superman, there's something for everyone.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aMass media and culturexUnited States. 0aMass media and culturezUnited States. 0aPopular culturexUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aPopular culturezUnited States. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aHistory : American History. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh1 aMadigan, Tim, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2016z978311149098440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846147240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438461472423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438461472/original  a978-3-11-149098-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles